// Document Manager
// CRUD operations for Markdown document files (.md) stored in a single directory.

An in-memory index maps document IDs to file metadata (path, lastModified).
Built at startup by scanning the documents directory. File size enforced via config.MAX_FILE_SIZE.
Documents may contain embedded review markup (comments, approvals, rejections) that getCleanContent strips.

FUNCTION DocumentManager.constructor(basePath)                                     EXPORT
  Store the base path for document storage.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.initialize() -> void
  Ensure the base directory exists, scan for .md files, and build the in-memory index
  with path and last-modified timestamp for each file.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.listDocuments() -> DocumentListItem[]
  Return id, name, and lastModified for every entry in the index.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.getDocument(id) -> Document | null
  Look up the id in the index. IF not found, return null.
  Read and return the file content along with metadata.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.saveDocument(id, content) -> void
  Throw if id not in index. Throw if content exceeds MAX_FILE_SIZE.
  Write content to file and refresh the lastModified timestamp in the index.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.createDocument(name, content) -> string
  Sanitize the name, throw if id already exists or content exceeds MAX_FILE_SIZE.
  Write the file, index it, and return the id.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.deleteDocument(id) -> void
  Throw if not found. Delete the file and remove from the index.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.getCleanContent(id) -> string | null
  Fetch the document, then strip all embedded review markers:
  status comments (approved/rejected), inline comment blocks, comment-start/end pairs,
  reject-start/end pairs, and approve-start/end pairs. Returns clean prose content.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.updateIndex(id, path) -> void
  Asynchronously stat the file and update (or add) the index entry.
  Used by the file watcher to reflect external changes.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.removeFromIndex(id) -> void
  Remove the entry from the in-memory index without touching the file.

---

FUNCTION DocumentManager.reset() -> void
  Clear the entire index. Call initialize() afterward to rebuild for a new storage location.
